# Anti-Hallucination Protocols for Enterprise AI Platform

## 1. NO FAKE LIBRARIES
- Only use standard, documented libraries: fastapi, pydantic, langgraph, langchain-groq, pymerkle, thefuzz
- Do NOT invent modules or use non-existent packages
- All imports must be verifiable through official documentation

## 2. STRICT PYDANTIC VALIDATION
- All FastAPI endpoints MUST use strict Pydantic BaseModel schemas
- Input/output validation is mandatory
- No exceptions to schema enforcement

## 3. SELF-HEALING LANGGRAPH
- If Groq LLM returns malformed JSON, StateGraph MUST route to Reflection/Self-Healing node
- Agent must diagnose schema mismatch, rewrite prompt, retry up to 3 times
- Fail safely after 3 attempts

## 4. TDD ENFORCEMENT
- Write pytest file for endpoint BEFORE writing FastAPI route
- Watch test fail first, then implement route
- All endpoints must pass comprehensive tests

## 5. ZERO-COST CONSTRAINTS
- Use only free-tier APIs and local CPU-bound libraries
- No paid services or GPU requirements
- All dependencies must be free-tier compatible

## 6. VISUAL SPECIFICATIONS
- Background: bg-[#F9F8F4] (soft cream/off-white)
- Accents: bg-[#115E59] (dark teal/forest green) with pill rounding
- Outputs: bg-[#0F172A] (dark slate) rounded terminals with monospace
- 3-column grid layout for cards
- Green "LIVE" badges for active features
- Orange "PREVIEW" badges for roadmap features
